<head>
  <title>PersistFile</title>
</head>

<body>

    <h1>PersistFile</h1>

        <p>This event interface handles the peristing of user entered configuration and delivery to interested parties.</p>

    <h2>Description</h2>
        <p>This event handler generates events for all persisted configuration at startup and when a subscribe is made for the data, it
        also listens for events to update this configuration data and saves the new value and distributes it.</p>

        The only configuration attribute is the name of the disk file to write the data to.

    <h2>Configuration</h2>
        <pre>
    &lt;eventInterface module='EventHandlers.PersistFile' name='PersistFile' persistFile='WebBrickGateway.xml'&gt;
    &lt;/eventInterface&gt;
        </pre>
</body>

</html>
